      "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/d/ea666f/{size}.png",
      "created_at": "2025-02-26T09:42:05.054Z",
      "cooked": "<p>More ore less the same here, but with Direto (afaik is the same as the Suito).<br>\nGo and check here, I maybe found a workaround, not ideal but it works for me:</p>\n<aside class=\"quote\" data-post=\"16\" data-topic=\"55093\">\n  <div class=\"title\">\n    <div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n    <img loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/d/ea666f/48.png\" class=\"avatar\">\n    <a href=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/t/solved-elite-direto-connection-gone/55093/16\">[Solved] - Elite Direto connection gone</a> <a class=\"badge-category__wrapper \" href=\"/c/resolved-bugs-and-issues/33\"><span data-category-id=\"33\" style=\"--category-badge-color: #3AB54A; --category-badge-text-color: #FFFFFF;\" data-drop-close=\"true\" class=\"badge-category \"><span class=\"badge-category__name\">Resolved Bugs and Issues</span></span></a>\n  </div>\n  <blockquote>\n    Yes of course it\u2019s not paired as \u201ctrainer\u201d: it only reads data as the Direto power meter is seen as a simple sensor. \nThe issue of TD (restart it multiple times before it gets the connection right) is seen with other trainers, I see in this forum.\n  </blockquote>\n</aside>\n",
